TopicTitle: Part not compiling, weird error in log file

Articles.Content:
Hello

I'm trying to get a new cockpit into the game, but it's not appearing in VAB parts list and there's this weird error in debug menu:

Log file:

https://www.dropbox.com/home/Problem?preview=KSP.log

I was able to set up internal model and then spawn it in Unity with parttools, so it's not completely broken. It's been a long time since I last did this so I might have forgotten some step in Unity set up.

Guessing here: the "Input string was not in the correct format" leads me to think it's an error in the config file. Looks like StringToNumber and ParseInt32  calls are complaining so I would look for either a typo in an integer or maybe a wrong parameter - giving it a string or a bool when it expects a integer.
